modules.description: Provides functions to construct and manipulate M-trees, including inserting elements, iterating over nodes and objects, and querying ranges. Operates on custom types representing tree nodes and objects, with support for user-defined equality and distance metrics. Used for spatial searches, such as finding points within a specific radius of a given location.

Inserts metric data incrementally and performs range queries based on user-defined distance functions. Operates on tree structures where each node contains entries with metric values and pointers to child nodes. Used for efficient similarity searches in applications like image retrieval and nearest neighbor queries.

Creates and manages a tree structure optimized for nearest-neighbor searches, using a specified branching factor, equality check, and distance metric. Operates on custom tree nodes and supports insertion, iteration, and range queries based on distance. Used to efficiently retrieve points within a spatial or metric distance from a given location.
